$ Simply supported beam — SOL 101 example
$ Geometry: 10m × 1m × 0.1m thick plate
$ Material: Steel (E=200 GPa, nu=0.3)
$ Load: 100 N central point load
$ BCs: Pinned at x=0, y=0; roller at x=10, y=0
$ Expected: δ_max = P*L^3/(48*E*I) = 100*1000/(48*2e11*1/120) = 3.125e-8 m
$
$ Hand calc:
$   I = t*h^3/12 = 0.1*1.0^3/12 = 0.008333
$   δ = P*L^3/(48*E*I) = 100*10^3/(48*2e11*0.008333) = 1.25e-5 m
$
SOL 101
CEND
SUBCASE 1
  LABEL = SIMPLY SUPPORTED BEAM MIDPOINT LOAD
  LOAD  = 1
  SPC   = 1
BEGIN BULK
$ ── Nodes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,2.5,0.0,0.0
GRID,3,,5.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,4,,7.5,0.0,0.0
GRID,5,,10.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,6,,0.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,7,,2.5,1.0,0.0
GRID,8,,5.0,1.0,0.0
GRID,9,,7.5,1.0,0.0
GRID,10,,10.0,1.0,0.0
$ ── Material ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MAT1,1,2.0E11,,0.3
$ ── Property ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PSHELL,1,1,0.1
$ ── Elements ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CQUAD4,1,1,1,2,7,6
CQUAD4,2,1,2,3,8,7
CQUAD4,3,1,3,4,9,8
CQUAD4,4,1,4,5,10,9
$ ── Loads ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
$ 50 N downward (y-dir, in-plane) at each midspan node
FORCE,1,3,0,50.0,0.0,-1.0,0.0
FORCE,1,8,0,50.0,0.0,-1.0,0.0
$ ── Boundary Conditions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
$ Pin left: fix x,y,z and rotations at nodes 1 and 6
SPC1,1,123456,1
SPC1,1,123456,6
$ Roller right: fix y only at nodes 5 and 10
SPC1,1,2,5
SPC1,1,2,10
ENDDATA
